==Dutch==
[[Category:Dutch personal pronouns]]
===Personal pronoun===
'''gij'''

# ''Second-person singular, subjective:'' [[thou]] (''dialectal'').
#: ''Verveelt gij u niet?'' &mdash; Aren't you bored?

====Related terms====
: ''See [[Wiktionary:Dutch inflection#Pronouns|Wiktionary:Dutch inflection]]''

====Usage notes====
The personal pronoun ''[[gij]]'' and its variants are now restricted to religious context, and are considered archaic in the [[Netherlands]]. In [[Flanders]], ''[[gij]]'' is still commonly used as the second-person singular. The best translation in both cases would be ''[[thou]]''. Unlike in English, ''gij'' usually doesn't take a different verb form than ''[[jij]]'', except when there is inversion or with some irregular verbs. Compare: ''heb jij dit gedaan?'' versus ''hebt gij dit gedaan?'' (have you done this?). Also: ''jij zal'' versus ''gij zult'' (you shall/will), ''jij bent'' versus ''gij zijt'' etc.